@node faq "Frequently Asked Questions"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                        Frequently Asked Questions
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

@{b}Q: How do I create Practice Levels with different Tribes?@{ub}

A: Simple thing this is... first  design  your  level  with  your  prefered
   tribe, then save it to disk (or copy it to your clipboard) and  load  it
   into your Practice world file.


@{b}Q: I have designed a level, but everytime I want to play  it,  my  computer
   crashes. What am I doing wrong?@{ub}

A: First check your level name for illegal characters (>127), then look  if
   you  use too many roundabouts or too many catapults/cannons. Also try to
   reduce  the chain lengths of cannons and catapults or temporarily remove
   them. If this isn't going to solve the problem, send me  the  level  and
   I'll try to find out what's wrong.


@{b}Q: I'm using Exits in my level, but somehow, the Lemmings  just  walk  past
   them. What the hell is happening? @{ub}

A: You probably have made a little mistake with solid blocks underneath the
   exit. Refer to the @{" Object Information " link objectinformation} on @{" Exits " link objexit}.


@{b}Q: The Blocker (or Attractor) Lemming doesn't work!@{ub}

A: The Blocker only works with the Classic  Tribe.  The  Attractor  doesn't
   work in the Classic Tribe (there had been no Attractor in Lemmings 1).


@{b}Q: I'm running out of objects all the time. I've used a lot of solid blocks
   and water.@{ub}

A: You're probably not using the sizing feature for solid blocks and water.
   Try  to replace single objects with one long object stripe. Or if you're
   registered, just run the @{" Object Optimizer " link m02001f}.

   If this doesn't solve the problem, try to replace solid blocks with fake
   ones (using Raw Blocks), where the player won't notice the difference.


@{b}Q: I've tried hard but I can't get past the first level(s). How can I  play
   the other ones without having made the predecessors?@{ub}

A: There's a cheat to play all the levels. On the Lemmings 2  Title  screen
   click in all four corners until you hear a "Let's go" sound (not the one
   from the music).


@{b}Q: Why do I lose 48 bytes each time I start and quit the program?@{ub}

A: This seems to be a bug in the amigaguide.library or the datatypes and is
   not a problem of the Editor itself.


@{b}Q: When I play Lemmings on my Computer, the sound effects disappear after a
   short while. What's wrong?@{ub}

A: Dunno, but on my 68060 it disappears if I  don't  turn  off  the  music.
   Might be a bug in the med replaying routine.

@endnode
