@node m000000 "Classic Tribe"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                               Classic Tribe
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

This is the Tribe found in the original Lemmings  1  game.  Normally,  this
Tribe  has  only  a  few  fixed Lemming types.

These are: Climber, Floater, Exploder, Blocker, Builder, Basher, Miner  and
Digger,  which  will  be  set automatically, when you create a new level or
world. But you can change this if you prefer to have other Lemmings.

@{b}Special Notes: @{ub}

  Do not try to use an Attractor Lemming in a Classic World. The effect  is
  quite harmless but very funny. Test it, but don't use it in final levels.

  This is the only Tribe where you can use the Blocker Lemming.

@{b}Lethal Traps:@{ub}

  - 10 Tons: Squashes one Lemming underneath...
  - Stone  : Squashes one Lemming underneath...
  - Flamer : Burns every Lemming going to deep into the flames...

@{b}Special Objects:@{ub}

  - @{" Water                   " link objwater}
  - @{" Solid Blocks            " link objsolid}
@endnode
@node m000001 "Beach Tribe"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                Beach Tribe
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

Just a normal tribe most of the others.

@{b}Special Notes:@{ub}

  If you add a sun, don't forget the animating Sun Eyes object. Try to keep
  clouds and the sun @{" transparent " link windows}.

@{b}Lethal Traps:@{ub}

  - Evac. Chamber: Sucks one Lemming inside, then evacuates the chamber...
  - Clamp        : Eats one Lemming.

@{b}Special Objects:@{ub}

  - @{" Water                   " link objwater}
  - @{" Solid Blocks            " link objsolid}
  - @{" Roundabout              " link objround}
@endnode
@node m000002 "Cavelem Tribe"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                               Cavelem Tribe
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

Lots of graphics in this tribe! If you want to create some  mean  traps  or
looks-like-if-it's-an-exit-but-isn't type of levels.

@{b}Special Notes:@{ub}

  There are two torch objects to make a level a little bit nicer...

@{b}Lethal Traps:@{ub}

  - Monster: Grabs one Lemming.

@{b}Special Objects:@{ub}

  - @{" Water                   " link objwater}
  - @{" Solid Blocks            " link objsolid}
  - @{" Roundabout              " link objround}
  - @{" Dino Catapult           " link objdinocatapult}
@endnode
@node m000003 "Circus Tribe"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                               Circus Tribe
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

This Tribe contains unbelievable many background objects... if you want  to
create a colourful, funny level, take this Tribe.

@{b}Special Notes:@{ub}

  It's probably better to set light bulbs after you  have actually finished
  designing the level to avoid running of @{" Object space " link objectinformation}.

@{b}Lethal Traps:@{ub} none

@{b}Special Objects:@{ub}

  - @{" Solid Blocks            " link objsolid}
  - @{" Roundabout              " link objround}
  - @{" Cannon                  " link objcannon}
  - @{" Trampoline              " link objtrampoline}
@endnode
@node m000004 "Egyptian Tribe"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                              Egyptian Tribe
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

I specially enjoy this tribe, especially because of the Sand Container  and
Toggle, which are never used in the original levels.

@{b}Special Notes:@{ub}

  The Sand Container needs some special care: There's  a  bug  in  Lemmings
  that  will  cause  the  game to crash under right conditions: If the sand
  reaches the opening hole of the Sand  Container,  the  game  freezes.  To
  avoid  this  bug,  always  make  sure that the sand can run off the level
  somewhere, or limit the time so that it can't reach this height.  Have  a
  look at the provided levels to get the grip of it.

  Moreover, the Lemh Eyes side  Object  cannot  be  used  due  to  aligning
  problems.

@{b}Lethal Traps:@{ub}

  - Lem Crusher: Kills one Lemming at a time.

@{b}Special Objects:@{ub}

  - @{" Water                   " link objwater}
  - @{" Solid Blocks            " link objsolid}
  - @{" Roundabout              " link objround}
  - @{" Trampoline              " link objtrampoline}
  - @{" Sand Container & Toggle " link objsandcontainer}
@endnode
@node m000005 "Highland Tribe"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                              Highland Tribe
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

Nothing  special  about  this  Tribe,  except  that  the  right  order   of
mushrooms'n stuff is not easy to accomplish.

@{b}Special Notes:@{ub}

  There are graphics for (I suppose) an 'Electric Telephone  Trap'  Object,
  but unfortunately, they aren't used in the game.

@{b}Lethal Traps:@{ub}

  - Audrey 2: Grinds down one Lemming at a time.

@{b}Special Objects:@{ub}

  - @{" Water                   " link objwater}
  - @{" Solid Blocks            " link objsolid}
  - @{" Roundabout              " link objround}
  - @{" Trampoline              " link objtrampoline}
@endnode
@node m000006 "Medieval Tribe"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                              Medieval Tribe
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

Just a normal Lemmings Tribe...

@{b}Special Notes:@{ub}

  This Tribe has a lot of Special  Objects...  just  in  case  you  need  a
  combination of them all.

@{b}Lethal Traps:@{ub}

  - Dragon: Burns down every Lemming that tries to walk along.

@{b}Special Objects:@{ub}

  - @{" Water                   " link objwater}
  - @{" Solid Blocks            " link objsolid}
  - @{" Roundabout              " link objround}
  - @{" Catapult                " link objcannon}
  - @{" Trampoline              " link objtrampoline}
@endnode
@node m000007 "Outdoor Tribe"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                               Outdoor Tribe
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

This Tribe has a lot of background graphics. Unfortunately,  there  are  no
Sand Container and Toggle Objects as could be expected by the Raw Blocks.

@{b}Special Notes:@{ub}

  The Plant Catapult is out of order as the action height is 8 pixels above
  the  lower bottom of the Object and so normally, the Lemmings don't reach
  it. The only way to get it to work is to let lemmings fall onto  it  from
  above, which is not that easy at all.

@{b}Lethal Traps:@{ub}

  - Frog: Eats one Lemming at a time.

@{b}Special Objects:@{ub}

  - @{" Water                   " link objwater} (two different anims)
  - @{" Solid Blocks            " link objsolid}
  - @{" Roundabout              " link objround}
  - @{" Plant Catapult          " link objdinocatapult}
@endnode
@node m000008 "Polar Tribe"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                Polar Tribe
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

This is the only tribe where you can use the Ice Skater Lemming. There  are
a special graphics which enable you to build some nice ski jumping tracks.

@{b}Special Notes:@{ub} none

@{b}Lethal Traps:@{ub}

  - Ice Machine: Creates an Ice Cube from a Lemming  falling  into it  from
                 above.

@{b}Special Objects:@{ub}

  - @{" Water                   " link objwater}
  - @{" Solid Blocks            " link objsolid}
  - @{" Roundabout              " link objround}
  - @{" Cannon                  " link objcannon}
@endnode
@node m000009 "Shadow Tribe"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                               Shadow Tribe
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

Lots of animated objects are in the Shadow Tribe. And, which is  even  more
enjoyable, there are Sand Container and Toggle Objects.

@{b}Special Notes:@{ub}

  The Sand Container needs some special care: There's  a  bug  in  Lemmings
  that  will  cause  the  game to crash under right conditions: If the sand
  reaches the opening hole of the Sand  Container,  the  game  freezes.  To
  avoid  this  bug,  always  make  sure that the sand can run off the level
  somewhere, or limit the time so that it can't reach this height.  Have  a
  look at the provided levels to get the grip of it.

@{b}Lethal Traps:@{ub}

  - Lem Crusher: Crushes one Lemming at a time.

@{b}Special Objects:@{ub}

  - @{" Water                   " link objwater}
  - @{" Solid Blocks            " link objsolid}
  - @{" Roundabout              " link objround}
  - @{" Cannon                  " link objcannon}
  - @{" Trampoline              " link objtrampoline}
  - @{" Sand Container & Toggle " link objsandcontainer}
@endnode
@node m00000a "Space Tribe"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                Space Tribe
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

Welcome to the only Tribe with Teleports Objects. Nice feature indeed.

@{b}Special Notes:@{ub}

  To find out which Teleporter beams to which  one,  have  a  look  at  the
  @{" Object information " link objteleports}. Attention: @{b}Never@{ub} place an odd amount  of teleports
  onto one Level! This will probably crash Lemmings 2 or  at  least lead to
  unappreciatable effects!

@{b}Lethal Traps:@{ub}

  - Airlock: Sucks all Lemmings into space.
  - Walker : Kills every Lemming that tries to pass.

@{b}Special Objects:@{ub}

  - @{" Solid Blocks            " link objsolid}
  - @{" Roundabout              " link objround}
  - @{" Teleports               " link objteleports}
@endnode
@node m00000b "Sports Tribe"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                               Sports Tribe
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

This is the only Tribe which utilizies Steam Leaks and Toggles. It opens  a
whole new world of possibilities to create more interactive levels.

@{b}Special Notes:@{ub}

  To find out which Toggle controls which Steam Leak, have a  look  at  the
  @{" Object information " link objsteam}.

@{b}Lethal Traps:@{ub}

  - Tennis ball: Kills every Lemmings that goes underneath.

@{b}Special Objects:@{ub}

  - @{" Water                   " link objwater}
  - @{" Solid Blocks            " link objsolid}
  - @{" Roundabout              " link objround}
  - @{" Trampoline              " link objtrampoline}
  - @{" Steam Leak & Toggle     " link objsteam}
@endnode
@node m00000d "Practice"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                 Practice
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

If you select this menu item, you can create levels, that can be  used  for
practising.  For  most  of  the  Level  Prefs  are  overwritten from within
Lemmings 2, those gadgets are disabled. Please note, that there is no  need
to place an Exit Object.

Also note that there are only four levels  you  can  create  per  file.  In
Lemmings 2, they will always be used in this order:

1: @{" Space Training Level    " link m00000a}
2: @{" Medieval Training Level " link m000006}
3: @{" Egyptian Training Level " link m000004}
4: @{" Polar Training Level    " link m000008}
@endnode
@node m00021f "Menu Item: Open World"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                           Menu Item: Open World
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

After you've @{" selected your tribe " link m00001f}, you can either start painting on a new
world  file or open a previously created world, which can be done with this
menu item. If you  decide  to  load  an  old  world,  the  first  level  is
automatically  selected and displaced. You can have up to 8 world files per
Tribe, each one containing 10 levels.
@endnode
@node m00031f "Menu Item: Save World"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                           Menu Item: Save World
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

If you want to save a world file to disk again, you can do this  with  this
option.  It  saves  the  current  world  under  it's  old name. You cannot,
however, overwrite the original levels.  Use  the  @{" Save World as... " link m00041f} menu
item, to save a world under a different name.

If this menu item is disabled, you either have selected the original  world
or  created  a new world and haven't given it a name using Save World as...
before.
@endnode
@node m00041f "Menu Item: Save World as..."
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                        Menu Item: Save World as...
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

Saves a world back to disk, giving you the option to rename the world.  You
don't  need  to  append the .wld extension, it will added automatically, if
it's ommitted. Please don't try to overwrite the original Lemmings 2  world
file.
@endnode
@node m00051f "Menu Item: Update Catalogs"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                        Menu Item: Update Catalogs
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

You normally don't need this option: It examines all Tribe directories  and
creates the catalog files, which contain the list of world files available.

You have to do this only, if  you  rename,  delete  or  add  a  world  file
manually.
@endnode
@node m00071f "Menu Item: Select Level"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                          Menu Item: Select Level
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

This menu item holds the names of the 10 levels  in  the  currently  loaded
world. By selecting any of these sub-items, the chosen level will be loaded
into the editor screen.

After you have made your changes to this level, you can have  to  write  it
back to make the changes permanent.
@endnode
@node m00081f "Menu Item: Writeback Level"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                        Menu Item: Writeback Level
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

If you have made changes to a level, you have to write it back to the world
file  to make them permanent. This can be done using this option. Note that
to test a level, you need to first write back the level, and then save  the
world to disk before running Lemmings.

@{b}@{u}LIMITATION IN UNREGISTERED VERSION:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}Writeback always overwrites Level 1, so it's not possible  to  create  more
than 1 level.@{ub}
@endnode
@node m00091f "Menu Item: Overwrite Level"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                        Menu Item: Overwrite Level
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

Allows you to overwrite the selected  level  with  the  current  one.  This
allows you to change the order of the levels more easily.

@{b}NOT POSSIBLE IN UNREGISTERED VERSION!@{ub}
@endnode
@node m000b1f "Menu Item: About"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                             Menu Item: About
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

Shows the general blah blah... Also shows  the  name  of  the  owner  of  a
registered copy.
@endnode
@node m000d1f "Menu Item: Iconify"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                            Menu Item: Iconify
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

Closes all windows and screens and creates a small application icon on  the
workbench  screen. Also flushes the filecache and the undo/redo buffer when
the @{" Flush Cache Iconified " link m03061f} menu item had been checkmarked.

You can return to the editor by double clicking on the icon.

Iconify will fail, if:

- there's no icon for the program.
- icon or workbench.library are missing or cannot be opened.
- the Workbench screen is closed.
