@node m030400 "Menu Sub-Item: Solid Blocks"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                        Menu Sub-Item: Solid Blocks
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

Toggles the visibility of Solid Blocks on the map. Solid Blocks are  blocks
the Lemmings can e.g walk on.

Turning off the solid blocks makes the transparent blocks more visible,  as
they are no longer drawn ghosted.

Note that drawing on the map is only sensible while  actually  seeing  what
you're doing :-)

@endnode
@node m030401 "Menu Sub-Item: Transparent Blocks"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                     Menu Sub-Item: Transparent Blocks
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

Toggles the visibility of Transparent Blocks on the map. Transparent Blocks
are  blocks  the  Lemmings  cannot  interact with in any way, they are just
background graphics.

Note that drawing on the map is only sensible while  actually  seeing  what
you're doing :-)

@endnode
@node m030402 "Menu Sub-Item: Objects"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                          Menu Sub-Item: Objects
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

Toggles the visibility of Objects on the map. If this option is turned off,
you cannot manipulate objects anymore! However, if the @{" Object Indicators " link m030403}
are still turned on, you still can see their positions.

@endnode
@node m030403 "Menu Sub-Item: Object Indicators"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                     Menu Sub-Item: Object Indicators
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

Toggles the visibility of the Object Indictors on the map.  These  are  the
dragging and sizing nobs, aswell as the Level Size and View Boundaries.

Turning off the indicators won't stop you working with these  nobs  in  any
way, but you won't see anymore, which Object you have selected.

@endnode
@node m03061f "Menu Item: Flush Cache Iconified"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                     Menu Item: Flush Cache Iconified
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

As you might have already  read,  there's  a  built-in  filecache  in  this
program.  By  default, it uses up to 1/4th of the available fast memory. If
this menu item is checked, the cache gets  flushed  when  you  iconify  the
Editor, freeing as much memory as possible.

@endnode
@node m03071f "Menu Item: Interpolate Gfx"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                        Menu Item: Interpolate Gfx
---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

As you have probably read before, the graphics in the Block Elements window
are  halved  both vertical and horizontal to save space on the screen. This
shrinking process  leads  to  a  unavoidable  loss  of  detail,  making  it
sometimes hard to figure out what it is exactly.

Enabling this feature will interpolate each pixel, normally yielding better
graphics.  This,  however, will take some time to perform. Decide yourself,
which graphics suits you most.

@endnode
